  <h1></h1>
  <p>The statements which are used to execute only specific block of statements in a series of blocks are called case control statements.
<pre>
 There are 4 types of case control statements in C language. They are,

 1.switch
 2.break
 3.continue
 4.goto
 
Control Statement & Description

  <b>1.Switch</b>
     Switch case statements are used to execute only specific case statements based on the switch expression.
  <b>2.break statement</b>
     Terminates the loop or switch statement and transfers execution to the statement immediately following the loop or switch.

  <b>3.continue statement</b>
    Causes the loop to skip the remainder of its body and immediately retest its condition prior to reiterating.

  <b>4.goto statement</b>
  Transfers control to the labeled statement.</p></pre></p>
 
  
